This paper discusses a computational model for discovering organizing structures in conceptual representation, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model utilizes a hypothesis space and sparse connectivity, which are concepts commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses how the model can predict human property induction judgments, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and cognitive science (cs.CC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CC, and cs.NE.
